<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 03 at 4:33AM EST  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Heavy rainfall and isolated thunderstorms to impact Interstate 81
corridor and surrounding counties between Wytheville,
Christiansburg, Roanoke, Buchanan and Natural Bridge through 530 am
EST...
HAZARD...Through 415 AM EST...an area of heavy rainfall with
isolated embedded thunderstorms extends from Wytheville to
Pulaski to Christiansburg to Roanoke to Buchanan...or
roughly paralleling the Interstate 81 corridor from mile-
marker 70 to mile-marker 155. This area of heavy rainfall
will impact Giles, Craig, Montgomery, Pulaski, Wythe,
Roanoke County and City, Salem City, Botetourt, and Bedford
counties through 530 AM EST. Winds in excess of 40 mph are
possible with this activity.
SOURCE...Radar detected.
IMPACT...Heavy rainfall will result in ponding of water on roadways
and minor flooding in poor drainage and flood prone, low-
lying areas. Motorists should reduce speed, allow extra
distance between them and the vehicle in front of them, and
use low beam headlights. Avoid travel if at all possible.
Locations impacted include...
Roanoke...
Salem...
Radford...
Pulaski...
Christiansburg...
Blacksburg...
Wytheville...
Fincastle...
New Castle...
and Pearisburg.</description>
